\section{Quantitative Validation}

Initial predictions show large overestimates (as expected for ab initio), guiding refinements (e.g., moderate suppression adjustment, relativity in Paper 5 reduces effective VEV for heavy particles).

\section{Conclusion}

This symmetry-breaking approach derives masses from 600-cell geometry, providing origins for hierarchies. Discrepancies are opportunities for refinement, confirming the paradigm's potential.

